I12(1) all potential uses of reclaimed water, including, but not limited to, environmental restoration, fish and wildlife, groundwater recharge, municipal, domestic, industrial, agricultural, power generation, and recreation;

I12(2) the current status of water reclamation technology and opportunities for development of improved technologies;

I12(3) measures to stimulate demand for and eliminate obstacles to use of reclaimed water, including pricing;

I12(4) measures to coordinate and streamline local, State and Federal permitting procedures required for the implementation of reclamation projects; and

I12(5) measures to identify basic research needs required to expand the uses of reclaimed water in a safe and environmentally sound manner.

