I89. Definitions

I11In this chapter:

I79(1) Exceptional resource

I12The term ``exceptional resource'' means a resource of scientific, natural, historic, cultural, or recreational value that has been documented by a Federal, State, or local governmental authority, and for which there is a compelling need for conservation and protection under the jurisdiction of a Federal agency in order to maintain the resource for the benefit of the public.

I79(2) Federally designated area

I12The term ``federally designated area'' means land in Alaska and the eleven contiguous Western States (as defined in section 1702(T3oK) of this title) that on July 25, 2000, was within the boundary of_

I13(A) a national monument, area of critical environmental concern, national conservation area, national riparian conservation area, national recreation area, national scenic area, research natural area, national outstanding natural area, or a national natural landmark managed by the Bureau of Land Management;

I13(B) a unit of the National Park System;

I13(C) a unit of the National Wildlife Refuge System;

I13(D) an area of the National Forest System designated for special management by an Act of Congress; or

I13(E) an area within which the Secretary or the Secretary of Agriculture is otherwise authorized by law to acquire lands or interests therein that is designated as_

I14(i) wilderness under the Wilderness Act (16 U.S.C. 1131 et seq.);

I14(ii) a wilderness study area;

I14(iii) a component of the Wild and Scenic Rivers System under the Wild and Scenic Rivers Act (16 U.S.C. 1271 et seq.); or

I14(iv) a component of the National Trails System under the National Trails System Act (16 U.S.C. 1241 et seq.).

I79(3) Inholding

I12The term ``inholding'' means any right, title, or interest, held by a non-Federal entity, in or to a tract of land that lies within the boundary of a federally designated area.

I79(4) Public land

I12The term ``public land'' means public lands (as defined in section 1702 of this title).

I79(5) Secretary

I12The term ``Secretary'' means the Secretary of the Interior.

